# Raziel v5.4.6

## 🛠️ Fixes

### Reply Requeue Guard

Fixed an issue where replying to one of Raziel’s uploaded videos could accidentally trigger the bot to re-download and repost the same media.

Example problem:

```text
reply: "test"
→ bot reposted the original video
```

Cause:

Telegram includes portions of the replied-to message payload internally, which allowed the raw URL fallback scanner to rediscover the original media link.

---

## ✅ Changes

### Strict Reply Guard

Replies are now ignored unless the NEW reply message itself contains a fresh URL.

Allowed:

```text
reply + new youtube link
```

Ignored:

```text
reply + text
reply + emoji
reply + sticker
reply + random message
```

---

### Raw Payload Hardening

The raw fallback scanner now removes:

```python
reply_to_message
```

before searching for URLs.

This prevents nested Telegram payloads from re-triggering old media captions and links.

---

## 🎯 Result

Raziel no longer reposts videos when users casually reply to uploads.

Cleaner group behavior.
Safer auto-watch pipeline.
Reduced accidental duplicate downloads.

---

